<paragraph id="A9B71C9D1C8BBB9D1BF203AA1A97A4D2" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName id="22F2A19A6281FE73FA90ACE38138ECCD" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" status="stat. rev." subSpecies="azurea">Zygaena rhadamanthus azurea</taxonomicName>
Burgeff, 1914, Mitteilungen der 
<normalizedToken id="FA38B4EC871DDFD5430A2289604B77DE" originalValue="Münchener">Muenchener</normalizedToken>
Entomologischen Gesellschaft 5: 60, pl. 2, fig. 158, pl. 6, figs 75, 76 (
<taxonomicName id="5B27411E346BDC129A05A0B2B16F2D42" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. rev.">Zygaena</taxonomicName>
). Type-locality. France: Alpes-Maritimes (excluding coastal regions).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="724A286B9BD8E8776B5AC025CF16CF4B" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="32B813C16CF7E54BCCC71FA17221774A" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="177735BBEF4100DD86F2752FA7A371E5" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName id="953C3359375657B49E833874A9B22615" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis id="1B35768D90851C095A5708329DB9A4DC" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the 
<normalizedToken id="C5406DEF7E32DC958D65C96B765E9C05" originalValue="départements">departements</normalizedToken>
of Var and Alpes-Maritimes (excluding coastal regions). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="CD5239760EE8528F2E7B3BCA76C39248" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) synonymised this taxon with the melanistic 
<taxonomicName id="745A4F978B293116E1D2E7AC2B053B34" authorityName="Burgeff" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. stygia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="stygia">
<emphasis id="AE03346C6ABC297980E877630873101C" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus stygia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Burgeff, 1914, the distribution of the latter ranges from east of the River Var (Alpes-Maritimes) in France to Imperia in Italy. Much has been written about littoral melanism (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="041AB3A90134BF79D5A576768DD4C0D7" author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Biologisches Zentralblatt" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 23" refId="B4" refString="Burgeff, H, 1951. Die Meearalpengrenze der Zygaenen (Lep.), eine mit Hilfe der Populationsanalyse der Arten der Gattung Zygaena (Lepidoptera) durchgefuehrte Untersuchung ueber die Lokalisation und die Bedeutung geographischer Rassen in ihrem Zusammenhang mit der Eiszeit. Biologisches Zentralblatt 70: 1 - 23" title="Die Meearalpengrenze der Zygaenen (Lep.), eine mit Hilfe der Populationsanalyse der Arten der Gattung Zygaena (Lepidoptera) durchgefuehrte Untersuchung ueber die Lokalisation und die Bedeutung geographischer Rassen in ihrem Zusammenhang mit der Eiszeit." volume="70" year="1951">Burgeff 1951</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A407188169FF6B65982C6117A509549" author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Nova Acta Leopoldina (NF)" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 59" refId="B5" refString="Burgeff, H, 1956. Ueber die Modifizierbarkeit von Arten und geographischen Rassen der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.). Nova Acta Leopoldina (NF) 18 (127): 1 - 59" title="Ueber die Modifizierbarkeit von Arten und geographischen Rassen der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.)." volume="18" year="1956">1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="038D2BE6DFB15EBE6083B4DC7A3EEFDD" author="Burgeff, H" journalOrPublisher="Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse)" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 15" refId="B6" refString="Burgeff, H, 1965. Ueber die Bestimmung systematischer Einheiten durch morphologische und physiologische Merkmale, dargestellt an der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.) Nachrichten der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Goettingen (II. Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse) 1965: 1 - 15" title="Ueber die Bestimmung systematischer Einheiten durch morphologische und physiologische Merkmale, dargestellt an der Gattung Zygaena (Lep.) Nachrichten der Akademie der Wissenschaften in Goettingen (II." volume="1965" year="1965">1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5FB1904ED9728786068842EAD316923E" author="Dujardin, F" journalOrPublisher="90 e Congres des Societes Savantes" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" pagination="585 - 596" refId="B7" refString="Dujardin, F, 1965. Les voies de penetration des Lepidopteres dans le departement des Alpes-Maritimes. 90e Congres des Societes Savantes 2: 585 - 596" title="Les voies de penetration des Lepidopteres dans le departement des Alpes-Maritimes." volume="2" year="1965">Dujardin 1965</bibRefCitation>
: 586-587) and that exhibited by subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="A99E6C3D935E244C1082BAE03D8D635E" authorityName="Burgeff" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. stygia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="stygia">
<emphasis id="5E34FE8F0EA39F25A4DA88D52AA6E006" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">stygia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a good example for comparison with the 
<normalizedToken id="1B263BDFB8E508D5B4B54FD53DFCC9B1" originalValue="‘normal’">'normal'</normalizedToken>
phenotype of subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="00F499C717190A2C268749F86EE40CF9" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis id="3DEE304A1E4BC6AF6E73493AB5F05E14" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- to consider both taxa as one subspecies clearly disregards the concept of littoral melanism and the zoogeography of 
<taxonomicName id="6A18FA3BFDEAC06C499D1E8A7DEDDA8E" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis id="7F6260988BA76FDEA290E5BB67B38669" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in south-eastern France. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="881903D018A43C13DEF7A901AEBBF055" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. azurea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="azurea">
<emphasis id="13BD9C3168A660620777C654F4B8FCA9" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Zygaena rhadamanthus azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reinstated as a valid subspecies (
<emphasis id="04099F6F5E69B1FDAE1AF831EF754F1B" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">stat. rev.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
